Spain’s Salgado to Run for EIB Presidency, El Mundo Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-09-18T08:29:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/spain-s-salgado-to-run-for-eib-presidency-el-mundo-reports.html
Spanish Finance Minister  Elena Salgado  will run as candidate to become the next president of
the  European Investment Bank  to replace Philippe Maystadt when
he leaves the post at the end of the year,  El Mundo  said.  Salgado will leave her current post after the Spanish
general election on Nov. 20 and has already begun to make
“informal and discrete moves” to run for the position, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified people with knowledge of the
matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net  